<h1><span id="Alekhine.27s_Defence"></span><span id="Alekhine's_Defence">Alekhine's Defence</span></h1>
<p>At that point, it's unwise for White to take the d6 pawn, which means giving up the space advantage and allow Black to build his own pawn center.
</p><p>While 4. c4 is tempting, the modern variation 4. Nf3 gets better results, making harder for Black to equalize.
</p>
